name: FASTQ
description: FASTQ short read format ignoring quality scores.

name: BAM
description: BAM format, the binary, BGZF-formatted compressed version of SAM format for alignment of nucleotide sequences (e.g. sequencing reads) to (a) reference sequence(s). May contain base-call and alignment qualities and other data.

name: BED
description: Browser Extensible Data (BED) format of sequence annotation track, typically to be displayed in a genome browser.

name: bigBed
description: bigBed format for large sequence annotation tracks, similar to textual BED format.

name: bigWig
description: bigWig format for large sequence annotation tracks that consist of a value for each sequence position. Similar to textual WIG format.

name: TSV
description: Tabular data represented as tab-separated values in a text file.

name: bedgraph
description: The bedGraph format allows display of continuous-valued data in track format. This display type is useful for probability scores and transcriptome data

name: HDF5
description: HDF5 is a data model, library, and file format for storing and managing data, based on Hierarchical Data Format (HDF).

name: OME-TIFF
description: Image file format used by the Open Microscopy Environment (OME).

name: CSV
description: Tabular data represented as comma-separated values in a text file.

name: TAR format
description: TAR archive file format generated by the Unix-based utility tar.

name: ZIP format
description: ZIP is an archive file format that supports lossless data compression.
